The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Kamran under scanner
                                                   Kamran under scanner
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Rajasthan Royals left-arm pacer, Kamran Khan, has been reported for a suspect action. Rudi Koertzen and Gary Baxter, the on-field umpires during their IPL match against Chennai Super Kings in Centurion on Thursday, said they had concerns over Kamrans action and have asked for a review.         
	The two on-field umpires and TV umpire Amish Saheba reviewed the footage of the match and believed Kamrans action needed further scrutiny. The matter has now been referred to the IPLs technical committee.         
	The matter has now been referred to the team management of the Rajasthan Royals and the IPLs technical committee as per the laws of cricket that govern our game, an IPL statement said.         
	Kamran can continue to play until proven guilty. In five games he has taken six wickets at 20.66, limping off the field during his last over against Chennai Super Kings on Thursday.                                                                                                                       
